#
# Test-code amendments to the root .clang-tidy (clang-tidy inherits parent
# configs by default; this file only subtracts).
#
# bugprone-unchecked-optional-access cannot model GoogleTest assertions:
#
#   ASSERT_TRUE(opt.has_value());
#   EXPECT_EQ(opt->field, expected);
#
# is the canonical gtest idiom, but the check's dataflow analysis does not
# treat ASSERT_*/EXPECT_* as establishing that the optional is engaged, so it
# flags every guarded dereference in a test body. Rewriting hundreds of
# assertions to .value() would add noise without adding safety — a disengaged
# optional in a test fails the ASSERT first. The check stays enabled for
# production code, where the guard is a real branch the analyzer can verify.

Checks: '-bugprone-unchecked-optional-access'
